This paper discusses active learning methods and their effectiveness in various application domains. The paper focuses on analyzing query selection measures (QSMs) and their discrimination power within the current version space. This analysis is relevant to machine learning and artificial intelligence, which are covered by the cs.LG and cs.AI sub-categories. The paper also discusses the application of active learning in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV), which are covered by the cs.CL and cs.CV sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses heuristic search methods, which are relevant to the cs.DS sub-category. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CV, and cs.DS.
